      "code": "M15-E-VCG01",
      "label": "Purposive willing and intentional resolve (boulomai/bouleuō/protithēmi)",
      "context_description": "The term names the inner volitional act of purposive willing — Joseph's resolution to divorce Mary quietly, Pilate's will to satisfy the crowd, Christ's sovereign will to disclose the Father, the Spirit's will in distributing gifts, God's will that none should perish. The phenomenon is the inner act of forming and holding a deliberate intention. Inner-being phenomenon: purposive volitional willing.",
