      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 32505,
        "reference": "Rev 17:17",
        "strongs": "G1106",
        "translit": "gnōmē",
        "anchor_rationale": "'For God has put it into their hearts to carry out his purpose by being of one mind.' The gnōmē of the hostile kings is a shared inner resolution placed by God himself — the most revealing use because it shows the phenomenon (unified inner resolution) operating within God's sovereign overriding purpose. The kings have one gnōmē; God uses that gnōmē for his own ends."
      }
