        "reference": "Isa 14:24",
        "strongs": "H3289",
        "translit": "ya.ats",
        "anchor_rationale": "'The Lord of hosts has sworn: As I have planned, so shall it be, and as I have purposed, so shall it stand.' The irresistibility and finality of divine counsel stated with an oath. The verb (ya.ats) names the divine inner purposing that cannot be undone — what God has formed as intent will come to be, sworn by himself."
