    {
      "code": "M15-E-VCG04",
      "label": "Human counsel: seeking, giving, receiving purposive wisdom (ya.ats: human)",
      "context_description": "The term names the human counseling relationship — advisors sought, wisdom given, counsel rejected or followed, the counselor role as the expression of inner wisdom in the service of governance. Includes good counsel (Jethro, Hushai's counter-counsel), wicked counsel (Ahab's house), hostile counsel (enemies conspiring), and the prophetic refusal to give counsel when it will not be heard. Inner-being phenomenon: purposive wisdom given and received between persons.",
