        "reference": "2Sa 16:23",
        "strongs": "H3289",
        "translit": "ya.ats",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Now in those days the counsel that Ahithophel gave was as if one consulted the word of God; so was all the counsel of Ahithophel esteemed.' The most explicit statement of the counselor phenomenon: Ahithophel's inner wisdom was so accurate that receiving it was like receiving divine speech. The verse shows the entire phenomenon at its most concentrated — what counsel is, what makes it authoritative, and what its reception means."
