      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 130781,
        "reference": "Jer 29:11",
        "strongs": "H2803I",
        "translit": "cha.shav",
        "anchor_rationale": "'For I know the plans I have for you, declares the Lord, plans for welfare and not for evil, to give you a future and a hope.' The most significant divine devising verse. God's cha.shav is purposive and content-specific: plans for welfare, not evil. The phenomenon — inner purposive plan-forming — is at its most theologically significant here: what God has deliberated and resolved within himself defines the exile community's future."
      }
