    {
      "code": "M15-E-VCG06",
      "label": "Resolute purposing formed and executed (za.mam)",
      "context_description": "The term names purpose so firmly resolved that it cannot be revoked — human unified purposing (Gen 11:6, Tower of Babel), and divine irrevocable decisions (Jer 4:28, Jer 51:12, Lam 2:17). The phenomenon is the inner intentional act at its most fixed: what has been za.mam-ed has been purposed and will not be relented from. Inner-being phenomenon: irrevocable inner resolving.",
      "cluster_subgroup_code": "M15-E",
