      "anchor_proposed": {
        "vr_id": 21545,
        "reference": "Lam 2:17",
        "strongs": "H2161",
        "translit": "za.mam",
        "anchor_rationale": "'The Lord has done what he purposed; he has carried out his word, which he commanded long ago.' The za.mam is ancient, fixed, and now executed. The verse names the full arc of za.mam: the inner purposing preceded the event by a long time and was carried through without relenting. The phenomenon — irrevocable inner resolve — is shown in its complete form."
      }
    },
    {
      "code": "M15-E-VCG07",
      "label": "Deliberate inner attending: setting the heart (shit H7896K)",
      "context_description": "The term names the deliberate act of directing the heart's attention — setting the heart toward something, or the failure to do so. Pharaoh deliberately does not set his heart to the signs; the dying woman cannot set her attention to what is said; Absalom counsels Tamar not to set her heart to what happened; the psalmist takes counsel in his soul. Inner-being phenomenon: the deliberate directing of inner attention.",
