        "reference": "Exo 7:23",
        "strongs": "H7896K",
        "translit": "shit",
        "anchor_rationale": "'Pharaoh turned and went into his house, and he did not take even this to heart.' The negative instance is the most diagnostic: not setting the heart to the signs is a deliberate act of non-attending, not mere ignorance. The term reveals the phenomenon by its absence — the inner attending that could have been directed toward God's act was withheld."
