    {
      "code": "M15-E-VCG08",
      "label": "Foresight, provision, and the rational planning faculty",
      "context_description": "The term names the inner capacity for purposive foresight — the governor's capacity to plan for his community's welfare (pronoia), the person who makes provision for the flesh's desires, Qoheleth's quest for the rational scheme of things (chesh.bon), thought as a capacity belonging only to the living, and the divine inner attending being appealed to by a desperate captain. Inner-being phenomenon: rational planning capacity and purposive foresight.",
